&lt;p&gt;&lt;img width="800" src="/images/pkgng_image.jpg"&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;pkgng&lt;/strong&gt; is new version of package manager to install, upgrade and remove packages from FreeBSD system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Requirements&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;FreeBSD 9.1 or newer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Installation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;pkgng&lt;/strong&gt; must be install from ports to get latest version&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On terminal:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;kbd&gt; cd /usr/ports/ports-mgmt/pkg &lt;/kbd&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;kbd&gt;make&lt;/kbd&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;kbd&gt;make install clean&lt;/kbd&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;One pkgng is installed one must convert existing pkg database to newwer format.&lt;/em&gt;
  &lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;In case of Major conflict for package just reinstall that particular package from pkgng&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;kbd&gt;pkg2ng&lt;/kbd&gt;
  It will automatically take care of conflicts.
&lt;img width="800" src="/images/pkgng_conflicts.jpg"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Important: This will be irreversible step, Once done you can't use Older package management tools.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To make sure that your ports tree will also use same &lt;strong&gt;pkgng&lt;/strong&gt; tool, Update your &lt;em&gt;make.conf&lt;/em&gt; as follows:
  &lt;kbd&gt; WITH_PKGNG = yes &lt;/kbd&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Usage&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To get help
    &lt;kbd&gt;pkg help install&lt;/kbd&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Info for particular package
    &lt;kbd&gt;pkg info pkg&lt;/kbd&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Installing particular variant of the software &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;figure class='code'&gt;
&lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;span&gt;pkg_usage.sh&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href='/code/pkg_usage.sh'&gt;download&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;

&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;#!/bin/sh&lt;/span&gt;

pkg install curl

&lt;span class="c"&gt;# To install particular version/variant of software&lt;/span&gt;
pkg search PKGNAME

&lt;span class="c"&gt;#This will show all available packages&lt;/span&gt;
pkg install PKGNAME_VARIANT

&lt;span class="c"&gt;#To see all the installed packages&lt;/span&gt;
pkg info

&lt;span class="c"&gt;#Remove package from the system&lt;/span&gt;
pkg delete perl

&lt;span class="c"&gt;#Upgrade all the packages in pkgng database&lt;/span&gt;
pkg upgrade 

&lt;span class="c"&gt;#Check packages for known vunerabilities&lt;/span&gt;
pkg audir -F

&lt;span class="c"&gt;#Automatically remove Leftovers&lt;/span&gt;
pkg autoremove

&lt;span class="c"&gt;#To backup Package database&lt;/span&gt;
pkg backup -d DBNAME.db

&lt;span class="c"&gt;#To reinstall package&lt;/span&gt;
pkg install -Rf PKGNAME
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;/figure&gt;

